    "what_description": "Juniperus communis is a perennial evergreen coniferous shrub or small tree, native to the Northern Hemisphere. It belongs to the family Cupressaceae and is the only species in the genus Juniperus native to Europe. The plant grows up to 10 meters in height, with a broad, rounded crown and a short, columnar trunk, often developing a gnarled, irregular shape. Its leaves are scale-like, 2-4 mm long, and green to blue-green in color, arranged in whorls of 3. Juniperus communis produces small, berry-like cones, 6-12 mm in diameter, which are blue-black in color and contain 2-3 seeds.",
