    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Juniperus communis are attributed to its antioxidant activity, which helps to neutralize free radicals and protect against oxidative stress. The plant's antimicrobial properties, primarily due to the presence of volatile oils, such as terpinen-4-ol and sabinene, inhibit the growth of various pathogens and prevent infections. Juniperus communis also exhibits diuretic effects, increasing urine production and helping to alleviate conditions like edema and urinary tract infections. Furthermore, its anti-inflammatory properties, mediated by flavonoids like quercetin and kaempferol, reduce inflammation and alleviate symptoms associated with conditions like arthritis. Additionally, the plant's expectorant properties, resulting from the presence of saponins and volatile oils, help to relieve respiratory issues like bronchitis and coughs by facilitating the expulsion of mucus and phlegm.",
