    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Juniperus communis are sabinene, \u03b1-pinene, \u03b2-pinene, bornyl acetate, and \u03b2-myrcene, which exhibit anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antioxidant properties. Sabinene has been shown to inhibit the growth of bacteria and fungi, while \u03b1-pinene has demonstrated analgesic and anti-inflammatory effects. \u03b2-pinene, on the other hand, has been found to exhibit bronchodilatory activity, making it beneficial for respiratory issues. Bornyl acetate has been reported to possess sedative and antioxidant properties, and \u03b2-myrcene has shown potential in reducing inflammation and pain. These constituents work synergistically to provide the medicinal benefits of Juniperus communis, making it a valuable plant for traditional medicine.",
