    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Juniperus communis improperly include causing diarrhea due to its high content of volatile oils and terpenes, which can irritate the gastrointestinal tract and lead to excessive water loss. This can also trigger hypotension in susceptible individuals, as the sudden loss of water and electrolytes can cause a drop in blood pressure. Furthermore, the consumption of Juniperus communis may experience nausea and dizziness due to its potential to interact with medications or exacerbate underlying medical conditions. Additionally, the oil's ability to stimulate the digestive system can lead to abdominal pain in some individuals, particularly those with pre-existing gastrointestinal issues. These side effects are primarily attributed to the oil's high concentration of thujone and other bioactive compounds that can have unintended consequences when used inappropriately."
